---
alwaysApply: true
---

General style:
- use c++23 standard.
- use minimum comments, only if needed to explain some non-obvious things.
- use "auto func()-> ret" style of functions and methods.
- prefer "auto"
- each brace on the new line, unless it is some structure creating in one line.
- use 4 spaces for indenting
- use designated initializers as much as possible.
- some generic utility macroses and stuff in rendercommon.hpp

Rendering features:
- reverse-z depth
- usage of push descriptors
- usage of vkCmdBeginRendering
- Vulkan Memory Allocation lib for object allocations.

Build system:
- Custom build system through build.cpp in the root
- Compiler flags for clangd in compile_flags.txt (may be not full)
- Do not try to run it for you testing, I will manually do this
- thirdparty libs is located in external. Some of them is glfw, stb, vma
